{
  "texts": [
    "This table will guide a reader to the best appropriate GAN architecture for targeted biomedical images.",
    "In biomedical image analysis, the mode collapse problem is one of the severe problems that occur during the training of GANs.",
    "The mode collapse problem has a direct impact on the diversity of synthetic images generated by GANs.",
    "Synthetic images lack diversity as compared to real images.",
    "Due to this problem, the generator in the GAN misses salient features of the image and repeats the same features in the generation of new synthetic images."
  ]
}